Hash prefix budget stopping test
full window: transcript=10, coords=4, token_created=True
terminalized window: transcript=6, coords=2, terminalized=True, terminal_T=4, token_created=False
bounded-support window: transcript=6, coords=2, bounded_support_exit=True, token_created=False

negative controls:
- hash return before 2h coordinates: rejected (cannot return before 2h coordinates)
- append after prefix terminalization: rejected (closed window cannot accept more coordinates)
- bounded-support exit after full window: rejected (full window should return, not bounded-support exit)

Summary:
- a full labelled window can return one hash token
- a prefix that would exceed B_win terminalizes before adding a coordinate
- failed accumulation exits through bounded support without creating a token
